{"word":"ἔνερθε","slug":"ἔνερθε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔνερθε</b></el> <el>(before a vowel <el>-θεν</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <el>ἐν, ἔνεροι</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ὑπέρ, ὕπερθε</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <i>from beneath, up from below</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>without sense of motion, <i>beneath, below</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>οἱ ἔνερθε θεοί</el> the gods <i>below</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>dii inferi</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Preposition'><a href='S:Preposition'>prep.</a></a> with <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>beneath, below</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>subject to, in the power of</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}